student’s ability to be successful at UIC. When a challenging situation arises, a student or family may find it difficult to navigate the many resources and services that are available at the institution.      Health & Personal Concerns           Hospitalizations and Emergencies  Get assistance information on emergencies, hospitalizations, accidents, student deaths, and more             Mental Health or Self-Harm  Explore services available to students to support their well-being             Victims of Crime and Safety Concerns  Learn about the various resources to assist victims of crime          Health & Personal Concerns           Housing Instability and Food Insecurity  Find resources for students experiencing housing instability and food insecurity             Financial Concerns  Connect with resources that can help when finances impact your student status              Assistance    Back to main content           Academic Concerns     Academic Resources    Academic Grievances    Withdrawal    Emergencies and Absences      Health & Personal Concerns     Hospitalization & Emergencies    Mental Health    Victims of Crime and Safety Concerns    Housing Instability & Food Insecurity    Financial Concerns    Cannabis: Know the Facts      Campus Life    Faculty & Staff Resources     The Student Response Team    Behavioral Response Intervention Team      U & I Care     Meet Our Partners    Care Facts    News & Events    U & I Care Fund    U & I Care Plan                    UIC Logo        Office of the Dean of Students         DOS Offices    Career Services    Student Employment    Counseling Center    Wellness Center      For Employees    SA Human Resources    SA Technology    Leave Management    The Pulse      Safety    UIC Police    Office of Access & Equity    Contact-US    Giving         Contact   1200 West Harrison St., 3030 SSB Chicago, IL 60607  Phone: (312) 996-4857  dos@uic.edu        Social Media Accounts             UIC.edu links   UIC.edu  Academic Calenda